ion, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":10,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":19,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Roger de Miniott I was born about 1205, in Carlton, Yorkshire, England. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1250, in Carlton Miniott, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 46."},"et":{"about 1205–1250":"umbes 1205–1250","1230–1265":"1230–1265","1205–1250":"1205–1250","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","about 1205":"umbes 1205","1265":"1265","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","Carlton, Yorkshire, England":"Carlton, Yorkshire, England","Carlton Miniott, Yorkshire, England":"Carlton Miniott, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1205–1250":"noin 1205–1250","1230–1265":"1230–1265","1205–1250":"1205–1250","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","about 1205":"noin 1205","1265":"1265","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","Carlton, Yorksh